description:
&lt;p&gt;The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust Estates Department currently provides an in-house service provision for the Trusts’ Retained Estate and elements of maintenance and FM monitoring for the PFI facilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Following a recent review within the Estates Department an opportunity has arisen for the above post on a fixed term basis for 12 months.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For specific scope of this role please consult the job description and the person specification. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be professional and reliable and be able to carry out the list of duties mentioned in the job description.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a key member of a dedicated team you will work to ISO 9001:2015 Quality Standards and assist in the Estates Quality Development Process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Reporting to the Estates Supervisor you will be responsible carrying out the various maintenance duties throughout the Retained Estate and PFI Facilities, which principally comprises of three main sites at Dewsbury, Wakefield and Pontefract respectively.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
